name: MIPS-32
description: The MIPS processor was developed by Dr.John Hennessey and his graduate students at Stanford University in the early 1980s. It is currently one of the major processors in the embedded processor market.

name: Z80
description: The Z80 is an 8-bit microprocessor that was designed by Zilog and introduced in 1976. It became very popular in the late 1970s and early 1980s, especially in home computers and embedded systems.
